text: Aliabad Yek (, Romanized as Ālīābād-e Yek; also known as ‘Ālīābād) is a village in Deh Bakri Rural District, in the Central District of Bam County, Kerman Province, Iran. At the 2016 census, its population was 15, in 7 families. == References == Category:Populated places in Bam County
title: Aliabad Yek, Deh Bakri
